description: A bat found at Creative Minds Daycare in Brantford, Ont., has tested positive for rabies, resulting in temporary closure of the facility that cares for about 145 children as public health investigates.
title: Brantford, Ont., daycare closes temporarily after child finds rabid bat, hands it to worker

description: Firefighters in Spain, Portugal and Greece battled ongoing wildfires Friday, an important religious holiday in all three countries, as persistent hot, dry conditions challenged efforts to contain the blazes.
title: Heat wave hampers fight against wildfires in Spain, Portugal, Greece

description: The pilot of a helicopter that crashed into a lake Friday afternoon while helping fight a wildfire in Annapolis County, N.S., is conscious and has been taken to hospital for evaluation.
title: Pilot conscious after helicopter fighting wildfire crashes into N.S. lake

description: The Canadian pop star, who’s faced critical comments about her appearance on social media, has spoken out about embracing a “body neutral” mindset. Here’s what it means and how it differs from body positivity.
title: Why Nelly Furtado is embracing 'body neutrality’

description: Worldwide plastic production is on course to triple by 2060, but there are no immediate plans to resume efforts to create a legally binding global treaty to end plastic pollution.
title: Global plastics treaty negotiations fail to reach a consensus — again

description: Both Mexico and Canada have been subject to tariffs and tariff threats from U.S. President Donald Trump since he was re-elected.
title: Carney to visit Mexico next month as both countries navigate tense U.S. relations

description: When Jordan Cristillo remembers his brother Andrew, who died tragically in a car crash near Whitchurch-Stouffville earlier this month, he thinks of him as “a gift” — a loving father and a great friend. In the wake of his death, the Cristillo family is picking up the pieces and trying to ensure other families don't have to endure the pain they're feeling.
title: 'A huge community has a huge hole in it,' says family of father killed in crash north of Toronto

description: The shíshálh Nation says ground-penetrating radar has identified 41 additional potential unmarked gravesites at the former St. Augustine's Residential School on B.C.'s Sunshine Coast, bringing the total number of potential sites there to 81.
title: 41 more potential unmarked graves found at former B.C. residential school, shíshálh Nation says

description: Androids from 16 countries competed for gold in competitions such as 100-metre hurdles and kung fu at the 2025 World Humanoid Robot Games.
title: More than 500 humanoid robots compete in first world games in China

description: The family of a woman murdered by a serial killer in Winnipeg more than three years ago got the chance Friday to tell a court how deeply her death affected them – and, after years of the woman’s identity not being known, they finally got to say her name before a judge.
title: 'Screaming into silence': Ashlee Shingoose's father tells court of desperation in search for her

description: Jackie Bezos, who gave birth to her son Jeff at 17 and for a time raised him alone as she struggled to build their lives together, has died. She was 78.
title: Jackie Bezos, mother of Amazon founder, dead at 78

description: The Pokémon-esque prehistoric hunter had bulging eyes, razor teeth and a shark-like snout — and was small enough to fit in a single bed.
title: 'Deceptively cute' tiny prehistoric whale species discovered in Australia

description: The TTC is pursuing a sole-source contract with train-builder Alstom to deliver new subway cars for Toronto's subway system, the city announced Friday.
title: Toronto pursuing sole-sourced deal for new subway trains in wake of U.S. tariffs

description: Flash floods triggered by torrential rains have killed more than 280 people and left scores of others missing in India and Pakistan over the past 24 hours, officials said Friday, as rescuers brought to safety some 1,600 people from two mountainous districts in the neighbouring countries.
title: At least 280 people killed by flash floods in India and Pakistan, with scores still missing

description: At 5:34 a.m. the rocket blasted off in a flash of light, captured in a livestream posted to YouTube, from a base camp about 250 kilometres north of Mistissini, on Cree territory. Though questions remain around whether it reached space, the students say they're proud of what they achieved.
title: Concordia students send Starsailor rocket flying and enter the history books

description: A meeting between Canada Post and the union representing 55,000 postal workers has been delayed until next week due to the availability of federal mediators, the company says.
title: Canada Post and union meeting pushed to next week due to mediator availability

description: The Canadian Real Estate Association says home sales in July rose 6.6 per cent compared with a year ago, continuing an upward trend after the market had slowed in previous months.
title: Canadian home sales rose 6.6% in July compared to same time last year

description: In Hardisty, Alta., a critical hub for North America's oil and gas network, the future of the energy sector is shaping the debate around the upcoming federal byelection. While residents take pride in the industry, the town itself is grappling with a lack of services that is threatening its sense of community.
title: In critical North America oil hub, pipelines and uncertainty are shaping byelection

description: In Hardisty, Alta., a critical hub for North America's oil and gas network, the future of the energy sector is shaping the debate around the upcoming federal byelection. While residents take pride in the industry, the town itself is grappling with a lack of services that is threatening its sense of community.
title: Pipelines, policy and uncertainty shape Alberta byelection in Hardisty's oil hub

description: The Trump administration, stepping up its crackdown on policing in the U.S. capital, has named the head of the Drug Enforcement Administration to be Washington's "emergency police commissioner" with all the powers of a police chief — a significant move that the D.C. attorney general said was unlawful.
title: D.C. files lawsuit to stop White House from installing police commissioner for Washington

description: After more than two decades, a border security headache is finally over for a New Brunswick golf course tucked up against the U.S. border in the rolling hills of Victoria County.
title: How a long U.S. border headache came to an end for N.B. golf course

description: Manitoba Premier Wab Kinew is setting his government apart from neighbouring provinces by insisting he doesn't need Ottawa's controversial legislation to fast-track major resource projects.
title: Consultation, not legislation: How Manitoba's approach to major projects is different

description: Adam Ben David, a resident of Hampstead, Que., says everybody in town has a right to feel represented. The Israeli flag may leave some feeling left out, he says.
title: Hampstead, Que., resident challenges Israeli flag in front of town hall

description: Vast swathes of Canada's forests have burned in recent years. Here's what it takes to replant after a major wildfire.
title: Replanting forests after wildfires comes with complex challenges, but there are opportunities in the ashes

description: In Highest 2 Lowest, a loose remake of the 1963 crime-thriller High and Low, the director shows off his knack for framing New York City in a lively, exciting way, and touches on similar themes as the original, but doesn't quite stick the landing.
title: Spike Lee's Highest 2 Lowest drags down a Kurosawa classic

description: There's a lot of onus on women to stay safe in public spaces. And that's likely partly why a new police campaign in the U.K. aimed to stop men from harassing women runners in the first place is getting so much attention.
title: U.K. cops are going undercover as joggers. Will it stop women runners from being harassed?

description: As the U.S. enters its first peak hurricane season after a slew of cuts to the agency that handles most of the country’s climate and weather research and forecasting, scientists, emergency managers and lawmakers brace for uncertainty in Florida. They are also sounding the alarm about more proposed cuts to climate and storm research that could be implemented in 2026 and which could impact Canada.
title: U.S. braces for uncertainty ahead of peak hurricane season amid NOAA upheaval

description: The forward's two-year deal with the New York Sirens is the most lucrative one signed in the PWHL yet. She knows that comes with pressure to perform, but that's nothing new for Sarah Fillier.
title: With a lucrative multi-year contract in hand, PWHL star Sarah Fillier is chasing greatness
